<td class="answercell">
    <div class="post-text"><p>The statement is false. Consider, for instance, this polygon </p>

<p><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/JBk1c.gif" alt="enter image description here"></p>

<p>and choose the origin as your point.</p>

<p>Even if you restrict to points outside the polygon, it is easy to modify the counterexample, e.g.</p>

<p><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/EzCXH.gif" alt="enter image description here"></p>

<p>Your statement does hold for <em>convex</em> simple polygons, of course.</p>
</div>
    <table class="fw">
    <tr>
